\p  
\v 23 And Solomon had an end with his fathers. And he left after him of his seed Rehoboam, \sls (yea)\sls*, the folly of the folk, and made less from prudence; which \em Rehoboam\em* turned away the folk by his counsel. And Jeroboam, the son of Nebat, that made Israel to do sin, and gave to Ephraim \sls (the)\sls* way to do sin; 
\p  
\v 24 and full many sins of them were plenteous, for they turned them away greatly from their land, \em that is, sins great and horrible made them to be prisoners far from their land\em*. 
\p  
