\c 48  
\cl CHAPTER 48 
\p  
\v 1 And Elijah, the prophet, rose \sls (up)\sls* as fire, \em that is, burning in the fervent love of God\em*; for why his word burnt as a brand \sls (or as a torch)\sls*. 
\p  
\v 2 Which brought in hunger on them, and they pursuing \add [or follow-ing]\add* him were made few for \add [or by]\add* envy; for they might not suffer the commandments of the Lord. 
\p  
